numquam se leg-ibus. These words are omitted in ST, but it is obvious that they ought to stand in the text. Amphora is a frequent source of error in Mss.; here the eye of the copyist must have run from one numquam to another, with the result that he wrote originally numquam inermum inimicis, which was afterwards improved (as in ST) into numquam inermum se inimicis.
